reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Makes it so I can sit!!
reviews.reviewText: I have anterior pelvic tilt with rotated pelvis. It has gotten bad enough where I basically can't sit unless I have a lot of padding that is soft enough to compensate for the incorrectly distributed weight on my hips and pelvis, but still firm enough to offer support (pads that are too soft don't help me). This pads density and shape fits the bill! I've had plenty of seat pads over the years and this one has been by far the best. I carry it around with me from chair to chair as I can't sit for even a few minutes without it. I'd purchase more for every seat in the house but I'm hoping to correct the underlying problem instead.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Not the best for vehicles
reviews.reviewText: It’s great for a chair but I have a bad hip and lower back and need these anytime I sit and have lost my others places like borrowing wheelchairs in target and things like that, I’m pretty sure. I’ve kept a tight hold on this one and it works fine but you’re a bit high and it doesn’t really sink so I’m 5’5 and my head touches the ceiling of the 4Runner. And makes the area so enclosed I just deal with the pain. It’s a good product otherwise. I just need a different one that’s left in the car I think. I wish these things were cheaper or covered by insurance.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The only one that is soft enough!
reviews.reviewText: I have piriformis syndrome and ischial bursitis, with sciatic nerve pain. It’s excruciating and horrible, and I can’t sit anywhere. I have tried five different seat cushions, and this is the only one I can sit in. It is soft and squishy and supportive, and just right. All the others, even though they are memory foam, feel as hard as a rock. I like it so much, I’m buying another one. I hope my second one is just like my first!My second arrived very timely. And yes, it’s just as comfortable as the first. They are thick, too thick to use for the car. But now I have one at the kitchen table and one for my office desk.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I love this cushion! I actually use this in the car when I'm driving because it can be uncomfortable sometimes. My seat is better with the cushion, it helps with some of my lower back pain.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Soft, Comfortable, and Supportive
reviews.reviewText: I have been spending more time at our kitchen table, my new office, but the chair is starting to feel very uncomfortable. After a few hours, the chair feels like there isn't any padding at all, so I needed to find a solution. Luckily, I found the WANTELL seat cushion for desk chairs. Based on my usage and review, I am giving the WANTELL seat cushion a 4-star rating.The WANTELL seat cushion has a non-slip bottom which worked well while getting on and off the chair. And the cushion provided a lot of cushion which eliminated my sore tailbone. The seat cushion is fairly thick, so make sure you have enough space between your chair and the bottom of the table. It was not an issue in my situation, but could be a problem for some desk/table heights.The seat cushion contour made a surprising difference. The contour ensured there was extra cushion where you need it. The WANTELL seat cushion is a simple solution for a not so simple problem. Don't let the simplicity of the cushion cause you to overlook the design benefits. I recommend the WANTELL seat cushion if you need added support to eliminate chair fatigue.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for the office
reviews.reviewText: I've been using this chair cushion for about a month now and it has helped me sit for longer periods without pain. The cushion is ergonomically molded and is quite comfortable. The material on the outside is easy to wipe off and the inner cushion is sturdy and supportive. I highly recommend this product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars My Office Chair Has Had IT!
reviews.reviewText: I am in the process of doing my research on buying a new office chair, since I work from home and spend so much time a day sitting. It takes a lot to determine the right chair, so I decided to get this Desk Chair Cushion in the interim. The cushion is comfortable, but it would better if it was larger as it doesn't cover my entire seat. I do like the back side is coarse, so the cushion doesn't slide around in the chair. I have to position it just right for it to become comfortable. It's doing the job until I can get a new chair and then perhaps, I will find another use for it. I really don't have any pains to test it for pain relief, but it doesn't cause any. I felt it was a little pricey for a cushion, but it seems everything is high these days!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 2, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This cushion is very thick and plush. It might even be too thick, since it elevates me in my seat a bit. I personally like this, but know it might be a problem for others. The bottom of it has a grippy texture so it doesn't slide around in my office chair. Really like this! I'm a heavier person so can vouch for it if you're also heavier since it can be tough to find a cushion that can handle extra weight.

Very soft cushion, that fits my new desk chair. The reason for purchase, was the desk chair felt like I was sitting on plywood. The only thing I found odd, was the lack of company identification. Usually you get a pamphlet or at least a business card. But none with this. None the less I am very happy with the purchase.
